
## ✅ **50 Numbered Linux Commands with Explanation & Examples**

---

### 📁 File & Directory Management

1. **`ls`** – List files and directories
   ➤ `ls -l`, `ls -a`

2. **`cd`** – Change directory
   ➤ `cd /home/harshada`, `cd ..`

3. **`pwd`** – Show current directory
   ➤ `pwd`

4. **`mkdir`** – Create new directory
   ➤ `mkdir myfolder`

5. **`rmdir`** – Remove empty directory
   ➤ `rmdir myfolder`

6. **`touch`** – Create a new empty file
   ➤ `touch file.txt`

7. **`rm`** – Remove file
   ➤ `rm file.txt`, `rm -r folder/`

8. **`cp`** – Copy files or directories
   ➤ `cp a.txt b.txt`, `cp -r dir1/ dir2/`

9. **`mv`** – Move or rename files
   ➤ `mv old.txt new.txt`, `mv file.txt /folder/`

---

### 📄 File Viewing & Editing

10. **`cat`** – View file content
    ➤ `cat file.txt`

11. **`more`** – View file page by page
    ➤ `more file.txt`

12. **`less`** – Scrollable file viewer
    ➤ `less file.txt`

13. **`head`** – Show first 10 lines
    ➤ `head file.txt`

14. **`tail`** – Show last 10 lines
    ➤ `tail file.txt`

15. **`nano`** – Open Nano text editor
    ➤ `nano file.txt`

16. **`vi` / `vim`** – Open Vi/Vim editor
    ➤ `vi file.txt`

---

### 🔐 Permissions & Ownership

17. **`chmod`** – Change file permissions
    ➤ `chmod +x script.sh`

18. **`chown`** – Change file ownership
    ➤ `chown user file.txt`

---

### 💽 Disk & System Info

19. **`df -h`** – Show disk usage
    ➤ `df -h`

20. **`du -sh`** – Show folder size
    ➤ `du -sh myfolder/`

21. **`uname -a`** – System information
    ➤ `uname -a`

22. **`uptime`** – System uptime
    ➤ `uptime`

23. **`date`** – Show current date/time
    ➤ `date`

24. **`cal`** – Show calendar
    ➤ `cal`

---

### 🔍 Searching

25. **`find`** – Search for files
    ➤ `find . -name "*.txt"`

26. **`locate`** – Fast file search
    ➤ `locate config.json`

27. **`grep`** – Search text in files
    ➤ `grep "error" log.txt`

---

### 🧠 Process Management

28. **`ps aux`** – Show all processes
    ➤ `ps aux`

29. **`top`** – Real-time process monitor
    ➤ `top`

30. **`kill`** – Kill process by PID
    ➤ `kill 1234`

31. **`killall`** – Kill by process name
    ➤ `killall firefox`

---

### 🛠 Package & System Management

32. **`sudo`** – Run command as superuser
    ➤ `sudo command`

33. **`apt update`** – Update package list
    ➤ `sudo apt update`

34. **`apt install`** – Install a package
    ➤ `sudo apt install git`

---

### 🌐 Networking & Internet

35. **`wget`** – Download from internet
    ➤ `wget http://example.com/file.zip`

36. **`curl`** – Transfer data to/from server
    ➤ `curl https://example.com`

37. **`scp`** – Secure file copy over SSH
    ➤ `scp file.txt user@host:/path`

38. **`ssh`** – Connect to remote server
    ➤ `ssh user@192.168.1.1`

---

### 👤 User Management

39. **`whoami`** – Show current user
    ➤ `whoami`

40. **`users`** – List logged-in users
    ➤ `users`

41. **`groupadd`** – Create new group
    ➤ `sudo groupadd devs`

42. **`useradd`** – Add a new user
    ➤ `sudo useradd harshada`

43. **`passwd`** – Change user password
    ➤ `passwd`

---

### 📦 Archiving & Compression

44. **`tar`** – Create/extract tar archive
    ➤ `tar -cvf backup.tar folder/`, `tar -xvf backup.tar`

45. **`zip`** – Compress files
    ➤ `zip archive.zip file.txt`

46. **`unzip`** – Extract zip files
    ➤ `unzip archive.zip`

---

### 📜 Miscellaneous

47. **`echo`** – Print text or write to file
    ➤ `echo "Hello" > greet.txt`

48. **`history`** – Show command history
    ➤ `history`

49. **`clear`** – Clear the terminal screen
    ➤ `clear`

50. **`man`** – Show manual for command
    ➤ `man ls`
